Durban - A police officer has found himself on the wrong side of the law and is due appear in the Durban Magistrate's Court on a charge of corruption on Thursday. 

The officer, a detective constable based at the Sydenham police station, was charged by the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) on Wednesday. 
According to Ipid spokesperson, Moses Dlamini, the officer demanded R10 000 from a resident in exchange for making a case go away. 
